∙⁠ 
All the revolutionary features of the 36, packaged in a super-stout chassis, engineered specifically for modern hard-hitting, long travel, enduro-style riding. The 38 is hungry to devour all you can throw at it and ask for more.⁠
⁠
The newest addition to the fork family features 38mm stanchions, lower leg bleeders, air/oil channels, floating axle, arch shape and an elliptical steerer, providing maximum stiffness to weight. Tipping the scales with a starting weight of only 2180g— the 38 makes a strong case as a pound-for-pound great.⁠ 💪

[sound on] 🔊

A typical year for @yeticycles / FOX Factory Team athlete, Shawn Neer consists of 6 months of traveling the world racing on some of the most physically and mentally daunting tracks the @world_enduro has to offer.
⁠⁠
"As much of a bummer covid turned out to be in 2020. The silver lining turned out to be heaps more time training on local trails for race prep. I have never felt better on my bike and couldn't be more excited to get between the tape again. Bring on the race nerves and adrenaline. Looking forward to the 2021 race season with Richie and the team!"⁠⁠ -SN
⁠⁠
Shawn has taken to his backyard trails in absence of his usual international racing schedule. Repetition breeds muscle memory and speed that toes the line between fast as hell and dangerous.⁠⁠

node.text:
The Knife Edge ft. @gee_atherton⁠⁠ 🔪 
⁠⁠
On the heels of recent jaw-dropping big mountain projects, 'The Slate Line' and 'The Ridgeline', Gee once again pushes the envelope in his latest edit.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Unfortunately, this particular project didn't have the ending he was hoping for, but once again, Gee's nerves of steel and incredible ability to tame the gnarliest of exposure is on full display.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
"When people say that Gee is fearless they’re missing the⁠⁠
point. When you’re as passionate as he is about pushing the limits of the sport, fear is a constant. Overcoming that fear is what sets him apart." -@dan_atherton⁠⁠

node.text:
Track Walk in Maribor.⁠⁠ 🇸🇮🚶
⁠⁠
There is a bit of the old and a bit of new as riders took their first look at this year's World Cup track in Maribor, Slovenia. ⁠⁠
⁠⁠
This year's track showcases an all-new top section with a large triple, followed by some new loamy and rooted sections, featuring some interesting undulations. 

Athletes also reported some classic Maribor hard pack with the iconic rock garden, and a bottom section that has remained very fast and relatively unchanged⁠.
⁠⁠
"So far, the changes are awesome. (In the past) we've asked, 'take the track 6 feet right or left' and they've done it, which is cool because the track has been here so long, and it's been the same line over and over."-@bernard_kerr⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Tune in tomorrow as the puzzling begins after teams ride the new track for the first time for Practice.⁠⁠ 🧩 
∙⁠⁠
📷: @davetrumporephoto | @mrjacktennyson | @kenoderleyn⁠⁠
// #ridefox #mtb #fox40 #foxfloatx2 #uciworldcup #dhi #maribor⁠⁠ #trackwalk
